# Production deploy — manual only

**Never** run production deployment scripts on your own initiative (including after commits, “shipping,” or “we’re done”). The user must **explicitly** ask to deploy to production in that conversation turn.

## In scope (examples)

- [`Update-Prod-App-Backend.ps1`](Update-Prod-App-Backend.ps1) — git push + SSM to EC2 (`saathi-api`)
- [`Update-Prod-App-Electron.ps1`](Update-Prod-App-Electron.ps1) or any similar script that pushes code and updates production hosts
- Equivalent: `aws ssm send-command` targeting production app instances for deploy/restart, when used to ship app code

## Allowed without a deploy ask

- Local `git commit`, tests, builds, and **documenting** the exact command the user can run (e.g. “Run `Update-Prod-App-Backend.ps1` when ready”)
- Preparing a PR or describing deploy steps in prose — **do not execute** the deploy script

## When the user says “deploy to production” (or clearly equivalent)

Then you may run the appropriate script or follow the repo’s deploy docs.
